        <num>CHC 778</num>
        <heading>778.  Disposition hearing; evidence</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 778.  Disposition hearing; evidence
The court may consider the report of the predisposition investigation, any reports of mental evaluation, and all other evidence offered by the child, his caretaker or the state relating to the proper disposition.  The court may consider evidence which would not be admissible at the adjudication hearing.</p>
        </content>
